<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Eddee Ben'Wraa</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-20 13:46:44</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I have this robe, so I'll clear up some of the mess.  :)  The spawn is around 35 hours, give or take 6.  It could be 29, it could be 40, you never know.  The robe drops about 1 in 20.  That means only one robe per month drops.  Camping is useless, it's pure luck to get one.  You can sit there for 3 weeks without sleep never missing a spawn and still not get the robe.<BR>
<BR>
As for the price, they aren't selling on the Brell server.  The only robe on the game that's better for a 200+ int caster is the Kedge.  I'm a wizard with a 212 int with the robe, trying to fight my int down more and boost mana.  This robe is better than the carmine or cryosilk for me, at least until I can arrange my gear to where I can use the +int on those more effectively.<BR>
<BR>
I won't sell mine at this point, and probably won't ever sell it.  If I do, I know I can get well over 30k for it, maybe even 50k, at least on the Brell server.  Who cares about the +5cha (sorry enchanters heh), the +50 mana is the same as +50 int if you're over 200 int to begin with.<BR>
<BR>
Eddee Ben'Wraa<BR>
50 Wizard, Brell Serilis</font></td></tr></table>
